- have the server manage the location of the secure memory. It must allocate
  a free slot in process_clone() before it forwards the request to the client.
  It will only release a slot once the client tells is so from its exit
  function. We have to make sure that this information cannot be spoofed.

- check cookies. invalidate cookies when thread exits

- do we really need to go through the PLT and the GOT?

- avoid using wait4()/SIGCHLD, as it generates unneeded signals

- add 32 bit assembly

- get rid of __WORDSIZE, and use machine test macros instead

- rename all asm() labels to be more unique

- get rid of preloader and of ELF helper process

- clean up sandbox_impl.h, maybe create extra helper classes?
